# Normalize line endings on checkin so a contributor on Windows (this project
# is built with Visual Studio/MSBuild on windows-2022 in CI - see build.yml)
# doesn't silently reintroduce CRLF into files that are LF in the repo today.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Visual Studio writes .sln files with CRLF. `-text` (not `text eol=crlf`)
# is required to actually leave it alone: `eol=` still normalizes the
# git-object storage to LF and only converts to the given eol on checkout,
# which silently rewrote this file's stored form the first time anything
# re-added it under this rule (see PR #16) even though the working-tree
# bytes ended up the same either way.
*.sln -text

# Binary assets - don't let git attempt text normalization/diffing on these.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.ico binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.sketch binary
*.keystore binary
